Detailed Description

Special feature representing a settings value maintained by an application. If the value is changed by a Property Editor, the notification rule of the property specifies, when the application is notified. A Property Descriptor specifies how to present the property value.

Member Enumeration Documentation

anonymous enum

ID 

Reimplemented from Feature.

enum Property::Notification
 

Enumerator:
NotifyNever  Never notify the application of a change.
NotifyValidateSet  Notify the application before value is set to the property. If the application does not validate the value, it is not set.
NotifyPreviewChanged  For previewing the changed value.
NotifySet  Notify when value is set to the property.
NotifyCanceled  Notify when Property editor is closed.
